Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest transform

Purpose:
  Run a direct one-shot digest/export without creating a reusable `.sdpub` archive.

Usage:
  spinedigest transform [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--stage <planned|sourced|graphed|summarized>] [--verbose|-v]

Behavior:
  - Reads from `--input <path>`, or from stdin when `--input` is omitted.
  - Writes to `--output <path>`, or to stdout when `--output` is omitted.
  - May call an LLM depending on output format, target stage, and source state.
  - Does not leave a managed archive unless `--output-format sdpub` is selected.

Examples:
  cat chapter.txt | spinedigest transform --input-format txt --output-format markdown
  spinedigest transform --input book.epub --output digest.md --output-format markdown

Where to go next:
  - Prefer reusable archives:
    spinedigest import <archive.sdpub> <source>
  - Check active configuration:
    spinedigest config status
